questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a `PaymentService` is failing to roll back database changes. The code snippet is as follows: 

java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    @Autowired
    private AccountRepository accountRepo;

    public void processPayment(Long id, Double amount) {
        try {
            updateBalance(id, amount);
        } catch (Exception e) {
            // Log error
        }
    }

    @Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
    public void updateBalance(Long id, Double amount) {
        Account acc = accountRepo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
        acc.setBalance(acc.getBalance() - amount);
        accountRepo.save(acc);
        if (amount > 1000) throw new RuntimeException("Limit exceeded");
    }
}

Even when the `RuntimeException` is thrown, the balance update is still committed to the database.

You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput distributed gateway using `CompletableFuture` to aggregate microservice responses is intermittently 'hanging' or losing exception context. The code looks like this:

java
public CompletableFuture<Response> fetchAsync(Request req) {
    return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> client.call(req), customExecutor)
        .thenApply(res -> transform(res))
        .whenComplete((result, ex) -> {
            if (ex != null) log.error("Failed", ex);
        });
}

During heavy load, some requests never return a response to the caller, and no error logs appear.
